context: The original London production was scheduled to close on <a0_0>Saturday, 7 October<a0_0/> 2006, at the <a1_0>Dominion Theatre<a1_0/>, but due to public demand, the show ran until <a2_0>May 2014<a2_0/>. <a3_0>We Will Rock You<a3_0/> has become the longest running musical ever to run at this prime London theatre, overtaking the previous record holder, the <a4_0>Grease<a4_0/> musical. Brian May stated in 2008 that they were considering writing a sequel to the musical. The musical toured around the UK in 2009, playing at Manchester Palace Theatre, Sunderland Empire, Birmingham Hippodrome, Bristol Hippodrome, and Edinburgh Playhouse.
